                     <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d1">
                  Decorative designs:
                  <locus target="#1r #8r #15v #23v #34r #42r #48v #58r #70r #79r #85r #99r #112r #115v #122r #129r #142v #151r" facs="004 011 019 027 037 045 052 061 073 082 088 102 115 119 125 132 146 154">folss. 1r, 8r, 15v, 23v, 34r, 42r, 48v, 58r, 70r, 79r, 85r, 99r, 112r, 115v, 122r, 129r, 142v, 151r, </locus> (haräg);
                  <locus target="#7v #33v #41v #48r #57v #69v #84v #98v #111v #121v #142r #164r #165r #166r" facs="011 037 045 051 061 073 088 102 115 125 145 167 168 169">7v, 33v, 41v, 48r, 57v, 69v, 84v, 98v, 111v, 121v, 142r, 164r, 165r, 166r, </locus> (multiple full stops and a line of alternating red and black dots);
                  <locus target="#15r #78v" facs="018 082">15r, 78v</locus> (multiple full stops)
                  </decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                          <locus target="#150v" facs="154">Fol. 150v</locus>
                           <desc type="OwnershipNote">Concluding prayer mentioning owner:
                    Text: <foreign xml:lang="gez">ዝ፡ መጽሐፍ፡ ዘደጃች፡ አድማሱ፡ ወሰን፡ ወስመ፡ ጥምቀቱ፡ ኃይለ፡ ማርያም፡ ዘአጽሐፎ፡ በንዋዩ፡ በ፲ወ፱፻፵ወ፩ ዓመተ፡ ምሕረት፡ ጸሐፊሁ፡ ጌራ፡ ወርቅ፡ ወስመ፡ ጥምቀቱ፡ ተክለ፡ ጽዮን፡ ዘሀገሩ፡ ደብረ፡ ሊባኖስ።</foreign>
                    Translation: “This book belongs to Däja[zma]č Admasu Wäsän, whose baptismal is Ḫaylä Maryam. He commissioned it with his money on 1941 Year of Mercy [= 1948–9]; the scribe [wrote the book] Gera Wärq, whose baptismal name is Täklä Ṣǝyon of Däbrä Libanos.”
                    </desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                          <locus target="#166v" facs="170">Fol. 166v</locus>
                           <desc type="OwnershipNote">
                             A note of ownership, by Däjazmač Admasu Wäsän, with: 1) elaborate information about the owner’s parents; 2) a statement of personal faith (see text and translation below); 3) a note gifting the Psalter to his son; and 4) a seal of ownership
                    Text: <foreign xml:lang="gez">ቀዳማዊ፡ ልደት፡ እምአብ፡ ዘእንበለ፡ እም፡ በመለኮት። ወደኃራዊ፡ ልደት፡ እምድንግል፡ ዘእንበለ፡ አብ፡ በትስብእቱ። አአምን፡ ፪ተ፡ ልደታተ፡ ከብረ፡ በተዋህዶ፡ ዛቲ፡ ይእቲ፡ ፍሬ፡ ሃይማኖትየ፡ ዘእመውት፡ ባቲ፡</foreign>
                    Translation: I believe in His eternal generation from His father without mother in His divinity and in His later birth from the Virgin without the father in His humanity: I believe in these two births. He was glorified in his union. This is the fruit of my faith and I will die with it
                    </desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">
                          <locus target="#ir(ecto) #iv(erso) #iir(ecto) #iiv(erso) #iiir(ecto) #iiiv(erso)" facs="001 002 002 003 004">Fols. ir(ecto), iv(erso), iir(ecto), iiv(erso), iiir(ecto), iiiv(erso)</locus>
                           <desc>blank</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e2">
                           <desc>Identified in the insurance hand list as Psalter 5</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e3">
                          <locus target="#87v" facs="091">Fol. 87v</locus>)
                           <desc>text has been removed</desc>
                        </item>
